main event: Three bright disc-shaped objects with round domes were reported over Sioux City, Iowa on January 25, 1967.
interesting points: The objects moved in a straight line and disappeared to the northeast.
There was a noticeable pulsation or oscillation in the lights which was attributed to atmospheric conditions.
A 19-year-old boy named Gene Anderson claimed to have taken a Polaroid photograph of a saucer-shaped UFO in Sioux City on May 18, 1967.
The photograph was analyzed by the Air Force, but they could not determine if it was a hoax or a genuine UFO sighting.

Two teenage girls reported seeing a bright white light that turned into a circular object with a reddish-orange glow around the edge in Sioux City on February 9, 1967. The object was picked up on radar.
sighted object: three bright disc-shaped objects with round domes, a saucer-shaped UFO, a bright white light that turned into a circular object with a reddish-orange glow
witnesses: a farmer, a 19-year-old boy, two teenage girls
photographs: yes, the report includes a Polaroid photograph taken by the 19-year-old boy
